      • ParquetThriftBytesOutputFormat

        public ParquetThriftBytesOutputFormat(org.apache.thrift.protocol.TProtocolFactory protocolFactory,
                              Class<? extends org.apache.thrift.TBase<?,?>> thriftClass,
                              boolean buffered)
        The buffered implementation will buffer each record and deal with invalid records (more expansive). when catching an exception the record can be discarded. The non-buffered implementation will stream field by field. Exceptions are unrecoverable and the file must be closed when an invalid record is written.
        Parameters:
        protocolFactory - the protocol factory to use to read the bytes
        thriftClass - thriftClass the class to exctract the schema from
        buffered - whether we should buffer each record
